The paper deals with combinatorial properties of polytopes and their relationship with the complexity of optimization problems, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with discrete optimization problems and their polytopes. 

cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the combinatorial properties of polytopes, such as the number of hyperfaces, diameter, and clique number of the graph. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper investigates the relationship between the combinatorial properties of polytopes and the computational complexity of optimization problems. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with optimization problems and their complexity. 

cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of optimization problems, which is a common topic in game theory.
